  "text": "The three repos use distinct patterns for Prometheus metric registration:\n\n**kubernetes/kubernetes**: Wraps Prometheus types with a stability framework in `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/`. Custom types (Counter, Gauge, Histogram) in counter.go, gauge.go, histogram.go wrap `prometheus.NewCounterVec` etc. A custom `kubeRegistry` (registry.go) provides `MustRegister` with stability-level annotations and deprecation tracking. The `legacyregistry` package provides global convenience functions. Subsystems register metrics via `legacyregistry.MustRegister()` in init() functions or explicit Register() calls (e.g., restclient/metrics.go, workqueue/metrics.go, slis/metrics.go).\n\n**grafana/grafana**: Centralizes core metrics as package-level vars in `pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go` (counters, gauges, histograms, summaries). The `init()` function creates metrics using `prometheus.NewCounter/NewCounterVec/NewGauge` etc. and a helper `metricutil.NewCounterVecStartingAtZero`. The `ProvideService` in service.go calls `initMetricVars(reg)` and `initFrontendMetrics(reg)` with `reg.MustRegister()`. Individual packages also define their own metrics (authnimpl/metrics.go, caching/metrics.go, expr/metrics/metrics.go, etc.) using `prometheus.NewCounterVec/NewHistogramVec` directly.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus**: Uses the standard Prometheus client library directly with no wrapper. Two patterns: (1) global `init()` + `prometheus.MustRegister()` for process-wide metrics (cmd/prometheus/main.go, storage/remote/client.go, template/template.go), and (2) dependency-injected `prometheus.Registerer` passed to constructor functions like `newScrapeMetrics(reg)`, `newAlertMetrics(r)`, `newQueueManagerMetrics(r)`, `NewEngine(opts)` that call `reg.MustRegister()`. Key metric definition files span scrape/metrics.go, notifier/metric.go, web/web.go, rules/group.go, promql/engine.go, tsdb/head.go, storage/remote/queue_manager.go, and discovery/metrics.go.",
